## Early game

Mutagen Sample is a **Deimos regional drop** — the wiki classes it "uncommon"
on Deimos versus "rare" elsewhere, which makes Deimos the best sustained
source. Farm any endless Infested node — **Terrorem** (Survival) or **Hyf**
(Defense) — or run **Cambion Drift** bounties and free roam, killing in bulk.
These are in-mission enemy/tileset pickups, so a **Resource Drop Booster and
the Steel Path resource passive do boost them**.

No Deimos access yet (pre–_Heart of Deimos_)? **Naeglar** on Eris (Hive
Sabotage) drops a Rotation-B resource cache at roughly 15.5% for 3 samples — a
quest-free fallback, though the cache is an end-of-mission reward that boosters
don't affect.

## Mid & late game

**Steel Path Deimos** scales the same farm: denser, tankier Infested drop more
samples per minute, and the Steel Path Resource Drop Chance Booster stacks on
the in-mission pickups. Terrorem (Survival) or Cambion Drift on Steel Path is
the highest sustained throughput.

When you'd rather bank guaranteed caches, the Eris **Sabotage cache** nodes —
Naeglar, Candiru, Lepis, Psoro, Viver (Rotation B, ~15.5% for 3) — and
**Formido** on Deimos (Rotation A, ~14.3% for 3) each hand out a cache per run.
Caches are reward-table rolls, so only the Steel Path drop-chance booster
affects them, not resource boosters — squad size (each player's own cache roll)
is what multiplies them.

